column5: Trying to find some tire chains for my f150...  My tires are 285/60 r 18  The closer to Cornwall Ontario the better...
'cause he's gonna try to get up my laneway in 2 wheel drive Brian !!
I MADE IT WITHOUT THEM,WELL KINDA,YEAH I DID.  Good ol cooper tires did well.
My truck is stuck on the ice and there is 100 feet of slush stopping my from getting it out... And I don't have a winch either
i thought you couldn't have chains on your tires south of north bay?
I'm sure it's ok on the ice.
Ive called napa... Bensons... Canadian tire ... Ect... I can't even order em threw anybody...
Try car quest or a tire store they may be able to order some.

CORNWALL = Benson Auto Parts........It's their home base.  I KNOW that they can get them or prolly have 'em in stock.. I used to work for them and sold a TON or more of chains...prolly set you back around 150.00$  Have the counterperson call Arbrobec
